Allen-Bradley Co, a unit of RockwellInternational Corp, said it has formed a joint venture with TDKCorp of Tokyo to produce, market and sell ferrite magnets.    Allen-Bradley will be responsible for production and TDKwill handle sales and marketing. Products will be marketedthrough TDK Corp of America, a Chicago-based TDK unit thatmarkets TDK's electronic components.    The venture, to be known as Allen-Bradley/TDK Magnetics,will be based in Shawnee, Okla, in the existing Allen-Bradleymagnetics production facility. Reuter&#3;